import gsplot as gs
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib as mpl
import matplotlib.ticker as plticker

axes = gs.axes()

x = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
y = [1, 4, 9, 16, 25]
x2 = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
y2 = [1, 8, 27, 64, 125]

gs.Line().plot(
    0,
    x,
    y,
    label="y = x^2",
)

    0,
    x2,
    y2,
    label="y = x^3",
)

gs.style.Labels(
    [
        ["x", "y"],
    ],
)
